728336f-a.text:
Androvette Street, south side, west from Kreischer Street, showing the rears of houses. These were, in all likelihood,the homes of the workmen of the Kreischer Brick Company factory, which was nearby. On the extreme, rlght at the N.W. corner of Kreischer Street,is the old Neilsen's Hotel, later known as the Four Corners House.
May 3, 1937
P. L. Sperr
